text_explanation: Well to moderately differentiated hepatocellular carcinoma (Edmondson-Steiner grade II), invading the liver capsule, with secondary rupture, vascular tumor thrombus observed (MVI: M2), negative resection margin, surrounding liver tissue shows cirrhosis. Immunohistochemistry: AE1/AE3(+), Hepatocyte(+), Arginase-1(focal +), Glypican-3(+), CD34(capillarization), GS-6(+), CD31(capillarization), Vimentin(-), PD-1(-), PDL1(-).

Chronic cholecystitis. Immunohistochemistry: Hepatocyte(+), GS-6(weak+), Arg1(+), GPC3(+), CK7(-), CK19(-), CDX-2(-), PD-1(-), PDL1(20%+, control is good).
